00:19:06.646 --> 00:19:10.650
is about carrying a lot of worries with you wherever you go.

00:19:11.818 --> 00:19:13.987
I guess that's to be expected.

00:19:15.071 --> 00:19:16.447
So whatever happens in your life,

00:19:17.615 --> 00:19:18.950
don't worry too much.

00:19:22.620 --> 00:19:23.621
Okay.

00:19:25.790 --> 00:19:28.084
I don't know what you're worrying about these days,

00:19:29.168 --> 00:19:32.130
but it probably feels like the biggest thing in the world.

00:19:32.881 --> 00:19:34.591
And of course, that's understandable.

00:19:34.674 --> 00:19:35.925
When I was your age,

00:19:36.801 --> 00:19:40.054
I felt like the world was collapsing around me every day.

00:19:41.055 --> 00:19:43.725
But looking back,

00:19:44.350 --> 00:19:47.687
all those things I bawled my eyes out over…

00:19:48.438 --> 00:19:50.982
Turned out to be nothing?

00:19:51.608 --> 00:19:53.026
No.

00:19:53.109 --> 00:19:55.820
I'd be lying if I said they were nothing.

00:19:56.738 --> 00:19:58.948
But looking back,

00:20:00.617 --> 00:20:01.868
like pieces of armor,

00:20:02.493 --> 00:20:05.788
they stuck to me here and there

00:20:06.789 --> 00:20:09.000
and made me stronger.

00:20:10.710 --> 00:20:11.669
So, Eui-ju,

00:20:12.754 --> 00:20:15.423
just go at your own pace.

00:20:16.507 --> 00:20:19.469
Don't rush or push yourself too hard.

00:20:20.136 --> 00:20:22.263
Rest when you need to.

00:20:23.222 --> 00:20:25.141
I'll stay right by your side

00:20:25.683 --> 00:20:27.143
so that when you're tired,

00:20:27.226 --> 00:20:30.688
I can bring you a nice cold glass of water.

00:20:35.276 --> 00:20:36.694
Even if things are rough now,

00:20:37.487 --> 00:20:38.988
they will work out in the end.

00:20:39.906 --> 00:20:40.782
Honestly, they will.

00:20:41.658 --> 00:20:44.035
I've seen it for myself.

00:20:50.792 --> 00:20:51.918
Dad, I…

00:20:53.503 --> 00:20:54.504
To tell the truth,

00:20:55.296 --> 00:20:57.090
there's something I need to tell you.

00:21:02.512 --> 00:21:03.680
CHAPTER 45: HELLO, THIS IS IMUK

00:21:03.763 --> 00:21:04.806
What does she want to say?

00:21:05.348 --> 00:21:07.475
I don't know. Let's wait and see.

00:21:22.407 --> 00:21:23.825
Why are you doing that?

00:21:24.450 --> 00:21:25.702
What's this?

00:21:25.785 --> 00:21:27.787
If you stay like that, you'll hurt your knees.

00:21:27.870 --> 00:21:28.705
Get up.

00:21:28.788 --> 00:21:30.665
Mom, Dad. I write novels online.

00:21:33.418 --> 00:21:34.335
Novels?

00:21:36.421 --> 00:21:37.797
I was in eighth grade

00:21:38.923 --> 00:21:39.841
when I first started.

00:21:43.219 --> 00:21:44.554
Nobody ever reads them.

00:21:46.097 --> 00:21:47.473
But I enjoyed it.

00:21:50.143 --> 00:21:51.436
Writing novels

00:21:51.519 --> 00:21:54.105
and seeing the characters I created come to life

00:21:54.731 --> 00:21:55.940
was so exciting.

00:21:57.108 --> 00:21:59.694
So I kept writing.

00:22:00.987 --> 00:22:03.906
Even when I didn't want to get up in the morning or go to school,

00:22:03.990 --> 00:22:06.617
just thinking about writing at night gave me such a thrill.

00:22:07.827 --> 00:22:08.661
I…

00:22:10.747 --> 00:22:13.458
I know I'm not much good at anything.

00:22:14.876 --> 00:22:16.627
And what's more,

00:22:17.295 --> 00:22:18.796
I never particularly enjoyed anything.

00:22:19.964 --> 00:22:21.549
But for the first time ever,

00:22:23.217 --> 00:22:24.886
I found something I really enjoyed.

00:22:26.763 --> 00:22:27.680
And that was…

00:22:29.390 --> 00:22:30.725
writing novels.

00:22:33.227 --> 00:22:35.104
Writing novels of all things.

00:22:37.982 --> 00:22:39.525
I wonder who you take after.

00:22:41.152 --> 00:22:41.986
So,

00:22:43.029 --> 00:22:44.280
what's the problem?

00:22:45.615 --> 00:22:47.742
My latest work

00:22:47.825 --> 00:22:50.244
was really popular.

00:22:50.328 --> 00:22:52.830
It got a huge number of views and likes.

00:22:52.914 --> 00:22:56.375
And a famous publisher agreed to launch it.

00:22:56.959 --> 00:22:58.377
That's amazing.

00:22:58.461 --> 00:23:00.671
I'm so proud of you, my girl!

00:23:00.755 --> 00:23:01.798
But the thing is…

00:23:03.966 --> 00:23:06.928
the story was all about my teachers.

00:23:12.725 --> 00:23:13.976
I based my main characters

00:23:15.436 --> 00:23:18.523
on my teachers.

00:23:20.316 --> 00:23:22.401
People at school found out.

00:23:24.779 --> 00:23:27.156
And now the principal wants to hold a disciplinary hearing.

00:23:27.240 --> 00:23:28.074
What?

00:23:29.117 --> 00:23:30.952
This is my novel.

00:23:31.702 --> 00:23:33.955
I'm sorry. Wait until I'm in my room to read it.

00:23:42.338 --> 00:23:45.341
Why hold a disciplinary hearing over a novel?

00:23:46.342 --> 00:23:48.010
MURIM GIRLS' HIGH SCHOOL

00:24:01.649 --> 00:24:07.071
WE WERE FRIENDS HELLO, THIS IS IMUK

00:24:11.492 --> 00:24:14.954
Hello, this is Imuk.

00:24:16.122 --> 00:24:19.667
I wrote We Were Friends using traits

00:24:19.750 --> 00:24:21.586
of real people around me as inspiration.

00:24:22.670 --> 00:24:26.215
I dissected aspects of their daily life, their way of speaking, and their habits,

00:24:26.299 --> 00:24:30.636
and arbitrarily adapted them for my story.

00:24:31.762 --> 00:24:33.222
As a writer,

00:24:33.973 --> 00:24:36.017
I should've created something of my own,

00:24:36.100 --> 00:24:37.435
but I couldn't.

00:24:39.145 --> 00:24:41.063
I sincerely apologize.

00:24:42.273 --> 00:24:45.985
I've only now realized that my writing caused discomfort

00:24:46.068 --> 00:24:49.280
and hurt to others.

00:24:50.781 --> 00:24:53.701
I sincerely apologize.

00:24:57.121 --> 00:25:00.541
Writing this story made me very happy.

00:25:00.625 --> 00:25:02.126
I felt excited.

00:25:03.044 --> 00:25:06.964
But that happiness was built by borrowing from others,

00:25:07.048 --> 00:25:08.925
no, by taking from them

00:25:09.008 --> 00:25:11.177
without their permission.

00:25:11.260 --> 00:25:13.846
WE WERE FRIENDS

00:25:13.930 --> 00:25:18.059
To take responsibility for my actions, I will be deleting this novel.

00:25:19.143 --> 00:25:21.395
If the day ever comes when I can write again,

00:25:22.480 --> 00:25:23.814
I will think, reflect,

00:25:23.898 --> 00:25:26.025
and imagine on my own,

00:25:26.901 --> 00:25:29.278
so I can write something truly mine.

00:25:31.989 --> 00:25:33.574
Thank you for reading.

00:25:35.034 --> 00:25:36.244
I was so very grateful.

00:25:36.327 --> 00:25:38.996
HELLO, THIS IS IMUK

00:25:42.500 --> 00:25:44.001
Be it hate comments,

00:25:44.710 --> 00:25:45.670
no comments,

00:25:46.504 --> 00:25:48.339
my lack of skill,

00:25:48.422 --> 00:25:50.466
or the ridicule of those around me,

00:25:51.092 --> 00:25:53.928
I thought nothing could stop me from writing.

00:25:55.221 --> 00:25:56.722
I believed

00:25:57.848 --> 00:26:00.101
I could always keep writing

00:26:00.726 --> 00:26:02.853
and that I always would, no matter what.

00:26:05.398 --> 00:26:06.816
But now,

00:26:08.526 --> 00:26:09.485
I can no longer…

00:26:09.568 --> 00:26:11.946
DO YOU WANT TO DELETE THIS NOVEL?

00:26:14.907 --> 00:26:16.742
…be the same as I was before.

00:26:16.826 --> 00:26:23.666
"WE WERE FRIENDS" HAS BEEN DELETED RETURN TO MY TITLES

00:26:27.753 --> 00:26:28.713
We are gathered today

00:26:28.796 --> 00:26:32.049
to discuss the novel written by Yeo Eui-ju featuring her teachers as characters.

00:26:32.133 --> 00:26:34.677
We won't necessarily take your side.

00:26:34.760 --> 00:26:37.096
I believe if Eui-ju hopes to keep writing,

00:26:37.179 --> 00:26:38.597
she needs to learn something from this.

00:26:38.681 --> 00:26:39.515
She must be expelled!

00:26:39.598 --> 00:26:41.058
I told her to keep writing.

00:26:41.142 --> 00:26:42.435
I'm the one who's responsible.

00:26:42.518 --> 00:26:45.271
Mr. Ga won't be able to come to school for the time being.

00:26:45.354 --> 00:26:46.731
How bad is it?

00:26:46.814 --> 00:26:48.816
He didn't want to tell you for fear you'd worry.

00:26:48.899 --> 00:26:51.360
Mr. Ga, why did you do it?

00:26:52.611 --> 00:26:53.696
To me, you're…

00:26:55.948 --> 00:26:56.949
You're…

00:27:55.674 --> 00:27:57.676
Subtitle: Paul Carver

